---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout title="Start Local Proof" description="Run a local ShardLoom proof without package-publication or production claims." path="/start" active="start">
  <section class="page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Start</p>
    <h1>Start local proof.</h1>
    <p class="lede">Use the source checkout, run local smokes, and inspect evidence. This is not a package-publication or production support claim.</p>
  </section>
  <section class="section-grid">
    <div>
      <h2>Recommended first route</h2>
      <p class="narrow">Run the documented first-10-minutes checks from the repo, then move to certified local workload docs.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="code-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">PowerShell</div>
      <pre><code>python scripts/check_use_case_index.py
python scripts/check_use_case_coverage.py
cargo test -p shardloom-contract-tests --test release_readiness_metadata</code></pre>
      <div class="code-evidence"><span><strong>claim boundary</strong>local source-checkout proof</span><span><strong>fallback_attempted</strong>false where execution evidence is emitted</span></div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section>
    <div class="route">
      <article class="route-step"><span>1</span><h3>Read the first proof</h3><p>Open the repository first-10-minutes guide for exact commands and expected outputs.</p></article>
      <article class="route-step"><span>2</span><h3>Run local evidence checks</h3><p>Use the repo scripts and contract tests; do not infer release/package status from local source execution.</p></article>
      <article class="route-step"><span>3</span><h3>Inspect status</h3><p>Use the status matrix to distinguish runtime-supported, smoke-supported, report-only, blocked, and unsupported paths.</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
